s14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Cor. 9: 6-1 I. </div><div class="t m14f x60 h28 y2be ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16. </div><div class="t m96 x50 h28 y2be ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does the apostle show that the ministry </div><div class="t m177 x74 h28 ye1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">should be supported ? Verses 13, 14. </div><div class="t m14f x60 h28 y63 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17. </div><div class="t m41e x59 h28 y62 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Does not the apostle show from this that it </div><div class="t m41f x74 h28 y180 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is just as important to support the worthy laborer </div><div class="t m420 x74 h28 y368 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the gospel as it was formerly to support the </div><div class="t m8d x74 h28 y369 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priesthood ? </div><div class="t m421 x8b h28 y3bd ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t m2e7 x60 h28 y3be ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IN a certain sense, everything we have and are </div><div class="t m422 x74 h28 y3bf ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">belongs to God; but there are some things that be-</div><div class="t m423 x74 h28 y3c0 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">long to him in a special sense. Tnose things </div><div class="t m424 x74 h28 y3c1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which he has never given to man for his own use </div><div class="t m425 x74 h28 y3c2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are God&apos;s and his alone. The Sabbath, the tithe, </div><div class="t m426 x74 h28 y2c9 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and the first-fruits in the former dispensation, illus-</div><div class="t m427 x74 h28 y3c3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trate this fact. God has also permitted men to </div><div class="t m21e x74 h28 y3c4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">make gifts to him, and to consecrate a portion of </div><div class="t m2b8 x74 h28 y3c5 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">their substance, their talents, or their time, es-</div><div class="t m428 x74 h28 y279 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pecially to his service. This the Lord also accepts, </